<br>
Firstly, I voted for no sponsor.  I don't think it serves any purpose other than to exclude people who don't have friends in the 'circle'.  Proof of quality is in activity and attendance.  Also why should having a sponsor affect how long the trial period lasts for?  This means that those who don't have friend's inside suffer.  That is not logical or fair.  Also, what responsibility does the sponsor have?  Do we have the right to remove the sponsor from SCARAB if the initate is malicious.  Without clear definition the sponsor system has little, if any, meaning or strength.  This in my opinion goes against the SCARAB ethos of openess and acceptability by introducing an exclusivity through nepotism.  SCARAB is not a guild, I think we have to remember that fact.  We are a co-operative of people who have a common goal of improvement.  Similar to a guild but with freedom to chose and also, in my opinion, an ideal implied through the points system, that members prove their worth by their activity, not by knowing someone.<br>
<br>
Secondly, I think that initiates should be given a month to become full members.  Maybe two weeks.  If they don't turn up enough then they don't get membership.  Another more radical idea is one of point deduction for members.  I.e. once a month we lose 1 raid point.  If raid points fall below -3 then the member is removed to a 'retirement' section.  This way we can keep track of active members etc.  I don't actually like this approach personally, because of the additional admin requirements for our heroic trio of Karolus, Sild and Goldark (who I appreciate very much and thank them for their hard work). But we need a system to filter the inactive.<br>
<br>
So in summary.  The sponsor system at present doesn't hold any strength because there is no real logic or framework to enforce it.  If we did have a framework it would go against SCARAB ethos, so let's bin it!  We need to filter the less active members.  Remember this is a co-operative, not a guild.  We only exist if members have active goals and are willing to support others in achieving their goals.  If someone is not active or participating, they are not part of the co-operative, even if they have gone through the correct channels.  And finally we need to ensure that the system does not overload the admin guys with more work.  Keep it simple!<br>
<br>
